This project is dual-licensed under the GNU Affero General Public License v3.0 (AGPL v3) and a commercial license.

### Open Source License (AGPL v3)

For open source projects and non-commercial use, this software is licensed under the **GNU Affero General Public License v3.0**.

**Key Requirements:**
- **Source Code Disclosure**: Any modifications or derivative works must be made available under AGPL v3
- **Network Copyleft**: If you run this software on a server and provide services to users over a network, you must provide the source code to those users
- **Attribution**: Copyright notices and license information must be preserved
- **No Warranty**: Software is provided "as is" without warranty

**Full License Text**: See [LICENSE-AGPL](LICENSE-AGPL) or https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.html

### Commercial License

For commercial use, proprietary applications, or when AGPL v3 requirements cannot be met, a **commercial license** is available.

**Commercial License Benefits:**
- **No Source Code Disclosure**: Keep your modifications and derivative works proprietary
- **No Network Copyleft**: Use in SaaS applications without source disclosure requirements
- **Commercial Support**: Priority support and consulting services available
- **Flexible Terms**: Customizable licensing terms for enterprise needs

**To obtain a commercial license**: Contact ecosystem@plasticity.cloud

### License Selection Guide

| Use Case | Recommended License |
|----------|-------------------|
| Open source projects | AGPL v3 |
| Academic research | AGPL v3 |
| Personal/hobby projects | AGPL v3 |
| Commercial SaaS applications | Commercial License |
| Proprietary enterprise software | Commercial License |
| Embedded systems/devices | Commercial License |
| When source disclosure is not feasible | Commercial License |

### Frequently Asked Questions

**Q: Can I use JARZ Maven plugins in my commercial application?**
A: Yes, either under AGPL v3 (with source disclosure) or with a commercial license (no disclosure required).

**Q: What if I modify JARZ Maven plugins for internal use only?**
A: Under AGPL v3, internal modifications don't require disclosure unless you provide network services to external users.

**Q: Can I contribute to the project?**
A: Yes! Contributions are welcome under the project's Contributor License Agreement (CLA).

**Q: How does this affect Maven builds?**
A: The dual license allows use in both open source and commercial Maven projects while maintaining commercial viability.

